/wiki\/Liu_Xiaobo#cite_note-10\"><span>[<\/span>10<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-nobel-announcement_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Liu_Xiaobo#cite_note-nobel-announcement-11\"><span>[<\/span>11<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-rthk-nobel_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Liu_Xiaobo#cite_note-rthk-nobel-12\"><span>[<\/span>12<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Liu_Xiaobo#cite_note-13\"><span>[<\/span>13<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He is the first <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Chinese_people\" title=\"Chinese people\">Chinese citizen<\/a> to be awarded a Nobel Prize of any kind while residing in China.<sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Liu_Xiaobo#cite_note-14\"><span>[<\/span>14<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Liu is the third person to be awarded the Nobel Peace Prize while in prison or detention, after Germany's <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Carl_von_Ossietzky\" title=\"Carl von Ossietzky\">Carl von Ossietzky<\/a> (1935) and Burma's <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Aung_San_Suu_Kyi\" title=\"Aung San Suu Kyi\">Aung San Suu Kyi<\/a> (1991).<sup id=\"cite_ref-wachter_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Liu_Xiaobo#cite_note-wachter-15\"><span>[<\/span>15<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Liu is also the second person (the first being Ossietzky) to be denied the right to have a representative collect the Nobel prize for him.<\/p>","name":"Liu Xiaobo","place_of_birth":"Changchun , Jilin, China","place_of_death":null,"text":"Liu Xiaobo , Peace, 2010","year":2010.0}